he first group of Syrians have now arrived in the UK.</p><p>\"We believe this ... scheme will make a real difference to the lives of some of the most vulnerable Syrians by giving them protection and support in the UK.\"</p><p>While the refugees who arrived today can immediately start to get on with rebuilding their lives and recovering from the trauma they experienced, there have been warnings that many Syrian asylum seekers who are already here are faring less well.</p><p>Since the beginning of the conflict, around 3,800 Syrians have arrived in the UK independently and claimed asylum in the UK. According to Home Office figures between 2011 and 2013, just under 2,000 were granted leave to remain. Many more are still waiting for an answer.</p><p>Hashem, a Syrian academic who studied in the UK and claimed asylum at the beginning of this year has been told by Home Office officials that they are experiencing a 'massive backlog' and that it will be at least a year before his case will be processed.</p><p>He said: \"When I ask the Home Office if they have assigned a case owner to me or when my substantive interview will be, they say: 'Sorry, sir, I cannot disclose that information to you.\"</p><p>He said that he had provided a lot of evidence to the Home Office about his disloyalty to the Syrian regime, a requirement for Syrians who request asylum here, but that it seemed to make no difference to his case.</p><p>\"I have become a hostage to the endless bureaucracy that deals with asylum seekers,\" he said. \"It has been enough for me to lose my home country, the least host countries could do is make our lives a bit easier now. My aim now is to know my fate in this country. Can I stay or not? I don't want to be an asylum seeker indefinitely.\"</p><p>Over 2.5 million refugees have now fled the conflict and, as a result, UNHCR is calling on governments around the world to help resettle 130,000 people over the next three years.</p><p>In 2013, the fourth highest number of asylum claims (1,669) came from Syria, after  Pakistan, Iran and Sri Lanka.</p>","headline":"Syrian refugees arrive in the UK as part of scheme to relocate conflict victims","trailText":"Several hundred of the most vulnerable victims of the Syrian war are expected to arrive over the next three months","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3npac","wordcount":"506","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-03-28T18:38:17Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/mar/25/syrian-refugees-arrive-uk-scheme-relocate-victims","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk-news/2014/mar/25/syrian-refugees-arrive-uk-scheme-relocate-victims","tags":[{"id":"uk/immigration","webTitle":"Immigration and asylum","type":"keyword","sectionId":"uk-news","sectionName":"UK news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk/immigration","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk/immigration","references":[]},{"id":"world/syria","webTitle":"Syria","type":"keyword","sectionId":"world","sectionName":"World news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/world/syria","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/world/syria","references":[]},{"id":"uk/uk","webTitle":"UK news","type":"keyword","sectionId":"uk-news","sectionName":"UK news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk/uk","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk/uk","references":[]},{"id":"politics/politics","webTitle":"Politics","type":"keyword","sectionId":"politics","sectionName":"Politics","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/politics/politics","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/politics/politics","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/news","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/tone/news","references":[]},{"id":"profile/dianetaylor","webTitle":"Diane Taylor","r2ContributorId":"27974","bylineImageUrl":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/24/1366808408255/dianetaylor_140x140.jpg","type":"contribut