 The long and the short of it is Rebekah and Cheryl stand or fall together.\"</p><p></p><p>Burke told the jury it was important to understand what the prosecution were alleging was a conspiracy and this by its nature involved more than one person.</p><p></p><p>\"You cannot conspire on your own. A conspiracy requires a minimum of two people,\" he said in his opening remarks.</p><p></p><p>Burke asked the jury to \"bear in mind throughout, Rebekah Brooks has consistently denied her part in this essential two-part conspiracy.\"</p><p></p><p>He told them that Brooks and Carter \"adore each other\" and stood \"shoulder to shoulder for 16 years\" and that the families of the ex-PA and former chief executive of News International were close.</p><p></p><p>The trial continues.</p>","headline":"Rebekah Brooks and ex-assistant 'stand or fall together', hacking trial hears","trailText":"Cheryl Carter's counsel asks jury to 'park' previous evidence heard and only consider the sole charge against his client","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/25/1395758803256/Cheryl-Carter-003.jpg","wordcount":"235","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-03-28T15:02:15Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/mar/25/rebekah-brooks-cheryl-carter-hacking-trial","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk-news/2014/mar/25/rebekah-brooks-cheryl-carter-hacking-trial","tags":[{"id":"uk/uk","webTitle":"UK news","type":"keyword","sectionId":"uk-news","sectionName":"UK news","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/uk/uk","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/uk/uk","references":[]},{"id":"tone/news","webTitle":"News","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/news","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/tone/news","references":[]},{"id":"profile/lisaocarroll","webTitle":"Lisa O'Carroll","rcsId":"GNL004691","r2ContributorId":"15275","bylineImageUrl":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2