 as the world's fastest marching band at next month's London marathon. Just pity the poor tuba player</p>","hasStoryPackage":"false","body":"<p>A brass band is absolutely guaranteed to make me cry, so it's a good job I'm not running next month's London Marathon else I'd be in bits. </p><p>On 13 April, Mike Lomas, a cornet player from Manchester, will be leading a 31-strong marching band to claim the world record as “the fastest marching marathon band”.</p><p>Mike 22, from Stretford, is the director of the Huddersfield Marathon Band, who were the world’s first and fastest marching band to complete a marathon in 2011. The band lost their record the following year to some German imposters who beat them by 22 minutes. Now they’re back to reclaim their title, aiming to finish the London Marathon in just seven hours and raise over £60,000 for national deafblind charity Sense.</p><p>“We congratulate the German team for beating our record and would encourage them to give it a go again after us if they are crazy enough. It’s definitely going to be tough – we’ll be giving our lungs a real work-out as well as our legs, as we’ll be carrying our trumpets, horns, trombones, cornets, drums and even a tuba along the track! But we’re bigger and stronger than ever and couldn’t ask for a bigger stage or audience anywhere in the world!”</p><p>They band are working hard towards their fundraising target and have managed to raise £45,000 so far. They also enjoy the support of Sir Patrick Stewart, former Liverpool manager Rafa Benitez and comedian Sue Perkins who have been photographed with the band’s bright orange hat to urge more people to sponsor them.</p><p><b>To sponsor the Huddersfield Marathon Band, visit: <a href=\"http://www.justgiving.com/HMB2014\">http://www.justgiving.com/HMB2014</a></b></p>","headline":"All hail the Huddersfield Marathon Band: can you imagine this lot blasting out Paint It Black at the 25-mile mark?","trailText":"Props to the Huddersfield Marathon Band, who ar